To avoid the risk of major outbreaks or epidemic spread occurring again once the initial efforts to “slow the spread” have been lifted, France or a region could safely move to phase II when all of the following criteria are met ( Fig. 1):
•
a sustained reduction in the number of cases 18 for at least 14 days 19 ;
•
the ability of public hospitals to safely treat all patients requiring hospitalization without resorting to crisis care standards;
•
the ability to test all persons with symptoms of COVID-19 The ability of public hospitals to safely treat all patients requiring hospitalization without the use of crisis care standards;
•
the ability to actively monitor all confirmed cases and their contacts.
